# Keep the local Next.js server running

For local preview, use `next dev` (or `npm run dev`) on port 3000 and **leave it running**.

## How to start the server

When starting (or restarting after the server is actually down), use a durable detached process so Cursor agent shells do not reap it (exit 137):

```
nohup npm run dev -- -H 0.0.0.0 -p 3000 > /tmp/monvera-next-dev.log 2>&1 &
```

Run that via the Shell tool with unrestricted/`all` permissions (`required_permissions: ["all"]`). Logs go to `/tmp/monvera-next-dev.log`.

## Do not do this after every edit

- Run `npm run build`, kill port 3000, then `next start`
- `kill -9` a healthy `next dev` process just to "refresh" after text/message/CSS/component changes
- Never kill a healthy server on :3000

## Prefer HMR

Message/JSON/CSS/component edits are picked up by Hot Module Replacement. Trust HMR. Never use build + `next start` for routine edits.

## When rebuild/restart is OK

Only rebuild or restart the server if:

- The user explicitly asks, or
- The server is actually down / not responding
